article.headline: Radford 82, N.C.-Asheville 74
article.story: RADFORD, Va. -- Art Parakhouski scored 31 points, including 16 of Radford's final 26 in an 82-74 win over North Carolina-Asheville on Saturday. With the game tied 56-56 and 6:52 remaining, Parakhouski made a layup and free throw to put the Highlanders (7-5, 3-0 Big South Conference) ahead to stay. Parakhouski, who came in as the nation's 10th-leading scorer, averaging 22.9 points, was 8-for-8 from the field in the second half and had all 10 of Radford's points during a stretch of 1:38 that left the Highlanders ahead 78-67 with 2:10 to play. The 6-foot-11 senior finished 12-for-13 from the field and surpassed 30 points for the second straight game. Radford, which also got 15 points and 11 rebounds from Laz Trifunovic, was 17-for-24 from the field in the second half but just 10-for-24 on free throws. Matt Dickey scored 15 points off the bench to pace the Bulldogs (3-9, 1-1).
